		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We describe how we used a data set of chorale harmonisations composed by Johann Sebastian Bach to train Hidden Markov Models. Using a prob-abilistic framework allows us to create a harmonisation system which learns from examples, and which can compose new harmonisations. We make a quantitative comparison of our system&apos;s harmonisation performance against simpler models, and provide example harmonisations.</p>
